3.1.31" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.1.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 1, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.1.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 1, 27</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.2.147" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 2, 147</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.234" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 234</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.288" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 288</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.98" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 98</bibl>. <emph>over --s</emph> == deeply; deep enough, though not kneedeep: <cit><quote>more than over --s in love,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. I, 1, 24</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a man may go over --s in the grime,</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.106" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 2, 106</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>over --s in blood,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 48</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>over --s in snow,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.326" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 326</bibl></cit>.
